  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Tonight, William begged Sophia for one more bedtime story before sleep, and I quietly sat in the doorway to listen too.",
      "zh": "今晚 William 睡前又求 Sophia 再說一個故事，我也悄悄坐在門口一起聽。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia began with her favorite opening line: \"Long ago, in a kingdom ruled by a wise old king and a lonely queen...\"",
      "zh": "Sophia 用她最愛的開場白開始：「很久很久以前，一個由睿智老國王和寂寞王后統治的王國裡……」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The queen, she said, planted a whole garden of roses outside her tower, believing each flower could carry a small wish up to heaven.",
      "zh": "她說王后在她的塔外種了一整座玫瑰花園，相信每一朵花都能把小小的願望帶上天堂。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One evening, a strange ghost appeared in the garden, though it turned out to be gentle rather than scary at all.",
      "zh": "有一天晚上，一個奇怪的鬼魂出現在花園裡，不過牠其實很溫和，一點都不可怕。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The ghost told the queen a lie at first, claiming to be a god sent to test her, but soon admitted the truth: he was simply a lost soul looking for a way home.",
      "zh": "鬼魂一開始跟王后說了個謊，聲稱自己是神派來考驗她的，但很快就承認真相：他其實只是一個找不到回家路的迷失靈魂。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The queen felt joy instead of fear, and she promised to help him, since even ghosts, she said, deserve a little kindness.",
      "zh": "王后感受到的是喜悅而不是恐懼，她答應要幫助他，因為她說，就算是鬼魂也值得一點善意。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Every night, she gave the ghost one rose from her garden, and slowly, rose by rose, he remembered pieces of his old life.",
      "zh": "每天晚上，她從花園裡摘一朵玫瑰給那個鬼魂，慢慢地，一朵一朵，他想起了自己過去人生的片段。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William asked if the ghost used to live near a temple, and Sophia said yes, actually, exactly like William had guessed.",
      "zh": "William 問那個鬼魂以前是不是住在一座寺廟附近，Sophia 說對，還真的就像 William 猜的那樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the hundredth rose, the ghost finally remembered his own name and gave the queen one last kiss of thanks before disappearing into the light.",
      "zh": "在第一百朵玫瑰的時候，那個鬼魂終於想起了自己的名字，在消失進光裡之前給了王后最後一個感謝的吻。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The queen was sad for a while, but she said the garden still made her happy, because kindness like that never really disappears.",
      "zh": "王后難過了一陣子，但她說花園依然讓她開心，因為那樣的善意永遠不會真正消失。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William said the story was a little sad but also a little wise, which is exactly the kind of thing Sophia's stories always end up being.",
      "zh": "William 說這個故事有點難過但也有點有智慧，這正是 Sophia 的故事最後總會變成的樣子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "As Sophia turned off the light, William asked one final question: could a lie ever turn into the truth, if you just believed it long enough?",
      "zh": "Sophia 關燈的時候，William 問了最後一個問題：如果你相信得夠久，一個謊言能不能變成真相？"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia said that was a very good question for a seven-year-old, and promised to answer it properly some other night.",
      "zh": "Sophia 說對一個七歲小孩來說這是個非常好的問題，並答應改天晚上再好好回答他。"
    }
  ],
